{{Infobox radio show | show_name = Freakonomics Radio | image = [[File:Freakonomics Radio.jpg|border|215px]] | runtime = Variable | presenter = [[Steven Dubner]] | announcer = | creator = Steven Dubner and Stephen Levitt | writer = | director = | senior_editor = | editor = | producer = | exec_producer = | rec_location = | rem_location = | oth_location = | first_aired = {{Start date|2009|06|01}} | last_aired = <!--TBD {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | num_series = 5 ({{as of|2014|9|lc=y}}) | num_episodes = 288 ({{as of|2017|6|1|lc=y}}) | audio_format = | opentheme = | endtheme = | website = [http://www.freakonomics.com/ www.freakonomics.com] | podcast = }}
'''''Freakonomics Radio''''' is an American public radio program which discusses [[socioeconomic]] issues for a general audience. The show is a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the 2005 book ''[[Freakonomics]]''. Journalist [[Stephen Dubner]] hosts the show, with economist [[Steven Levitt]] as a regular guest. The show is also distributed as a [[podcast]], and is among the most popular on iTunes.<ref>{{cite web |author=Kevin Smith |date=14 May 2012 |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/top-10-podcasts-to-feed-your-brain-and-ease-your-commute-2012-5 |title=Top 10 Podcasts to Feed Your Brain and Ease Your Commute |work=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref> Created in September 2010,<ref name=newfreak>{{cite web |title=New Freakonomics Radio Podcast |url=https://www.npr.org/rss/podcast/podcast_detail.php?siteId=148603480 |publisher=[[NPR]] |accessdate=13 May 2014}}</ref> it is a weekly podcast. From July 2018, production moved from [[WNYC]] to [[Stitcher Radio]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insideradio.com/free/freakonomics-radio-podcast-moves-to-stitcher/article_42aabc6a-4800-11e8-acfc-43e4fcce31fa.html|title=Freakonomics RadioPodcast Moves To Stitcher|publisher=InsideRadio}}</ref>; Alison Craiglow is the Executive Producer. The staff of ''Freakonomics Radio'' includes Greg Rippin, Greg Rosalsky and Harry Huggins. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://freakonomics.com/radio/radio-bios/|title=The Team|publisher=Freakonomic Blog}}</ref> ''Freakonomics'' is released at 11 p.m. on Wednesday each week.
A gameshow episode "Tell Me Something I Don't Know" was broadcast on October 6, 2014. The show was hosted at The Greene Space in New York City. In the show, selected audience members presented their ideas to host Stephen Dubner and a panel of three celebrity judges. The winner of the episode was a 12-year-old who competed alongside former New York Governor Patterson.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.thegreenespace.org/events/thegreenespace/2014/oct/06/freakonomics-radio-presents-tell-me-something-i-dont-know/|title = FREAKONOMICS RADIO PRESENTS: 'TELL ME SOMETHING I DON'T KNOW'|date = October 6, 2014 |accessdate = October 6, 2014 |publisher =The Greene Space |last = |first = }}</ref>
