'''Shah Salim Khan''' (born July 29, 1975) is a former [[Pakistan]]i politician and entrepreneur disqualified from the [[Gilgit-Baltistan Legislative Assembly]] for having defaulted on a loan by the National Bank of Pakistan. He is the son of the 6th Governor of [[Gilgit-Baltistan]], [[Mir Ghazanfar Ali Khan]].<ref>{{cite news | last =Haider | first =John | title =GB governor's son joins hooligan club| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''dailytimes.com.pk''| date =26 June 2017| url =https://dailytimes.com.pk/4727/gb-governors-son-joins-hooligan-club/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =GBLA- 6 by elections : PML-N candidate clinches victory| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''timesofislamabad.com''| date =11 September 2017| url =https://timesofislamabad.com/11-Sep-2016/gbla-6-by-elections-pml-n-candidate-clinches-victory | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Shah Salim Khan Wins GBLA-6 Seat from Hunza| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''gbee.pk''| date =| url =https://gbee.pk/2016/09/shah-salim-khan-wins-gbla-6-seat-from-hunza/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Salim Khan was born in [[Baltit Fort|Baltit Hunza]] and raised in [[Hunza Valley|Hunza]]. His father, Mir Ghazanfar Ali Khan was the 6th Governor of Gilgit-Baltistan.<ref>{{cite news | last =Mir | first =Shabbir | title =G-B governor’s son awarded PML-N ticket| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''tribune.com.pk''| date =6 May 2016| url =https://tribune.com.pk/story/1098094/g-b-governors-son-awarded-pml-n-ticket/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =| first = | title =Rivals agree to settle dispute: Sost dry port| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''dawn.com''| date =15 November 2006| url =https://www.dawn.com/news/219026 | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref> Khan passed through the [[International School of Islamabad]] from 1982-1994. He is a graduate of [[Bentley University|Bentley College]], [[Boston]] USA, from 1994-1999 with majors in [[Management]].{{Citation needed|date=October 2018}}
==Career== ===Enterpreneurship=== He was the former vice chairman of Pak China Sust Port Company Private Limited''.''<ref>{{cite news | last =| first = | title =Company officials blame each other: NBP loan scam| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''dawn.com''| date =12 February 2009| url =https://www.dawn.com/news/342984 | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref>
===Politics=== Salim Khan was an elected member of the [[Gilgit-Baltistan Legislative Assembly]] in the 2016 election.<ref name=":0">{{cite news | last = | first = | title =MLA Shah Salim Khan rubbishes news of ‘being disqualified by court’| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''pamirtimes.net''| date =23 September 2017| url =https://pamirtimes.net/2017/09/23/mla-shah-salim-khan-rubbishes-news-of-being-disqualified-by-court/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =HGISF delegation calls on Shah Salim Khan to discuss youth issues| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''pamirtimes.net''| date =14 April 2015| url =https://pamirtimes.net/2015/04/14/hgisf-delegation-calls-on-shah-sleem-khan-to-discuss-youth-issue/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref> He won the seat in September 10, 2016 that had been vacated by his father, from [[Constituency GBLA-6|GBLA-6]] within [[Hunza District|Hunza Independent district]] on ''PML(N)'' ticket.<ref>{{cite news | last =Mir | first =Shabbir | title =Rifts emerge in PML-N ahead of GBLA-6 by-polls| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''mountaintv.net''| date =| url =http://mountaintv.net/rifts-emerge-in-pml-n-ahead-of-gbla-6-by-polls/ | accessdate =17 September 2018}}</ref> In 2018 he was disqualified from being a member of the assembly after the National Bank of Pakistan petitioned for his disqualification in 2017, a year after his election.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gbee.pk/2018/09/governor-gilgit-baltistan-mir-ghazanfar-ali-khan-resigns/|title=Governor Gilgit-Baltistan Mir Ghazanfar Ali Khan Resigns {{!}} GBee|website=gbee.pk|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-15}}</ref> A decision was annonced in open court on 9 April 2018 to de-notify Khan as member of parliament and instruct the scheduling of a new by-election in accordance with law.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1400604|title=PML-N member of GBLA disqualified|last=Correspondent|first=A|date=2018-04-10|work=DAWN.COM|access-date=2018-10-15|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://pamirtimes.net/2018/04/10/mla-shah-salim-khan-disqualified-by-gilgit-baltistan-supreme-appellate-court-for-being-bank-defaulter/|title=MLA Shah Salim Khan disqualified by Gilgit-Baltistan Supreme Appellate Court for being Bank Defaulter|last=Pamir times|first=|date=10 April 2018|work=Pamir Times|access-date=15 October 2018}}</ref>
