'''Thomas Whitelock Kempthorne''' (c.1834&ndash;3 November 1915) was a New Zealand manufacturing chemist and businessman who co-founded [[Kempthorne Prosser]] in 1870 in [[Dunedin]]. He was born in [[Cornwall]], [[England]] c.1834.<ref name="DNZB Kempthorne">{{DNZB|title=Thomas Whitelock Kempthorne|first= Gordon|last= Parry|id=1k8|accessdate=September 2014}}</ref>

